100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 6, 1925, in the wake of recent tensions, the League of Nations convened to address escalating disputes in the Balkans, aiming to maintain peace in the region. Meanwhile, the United States continued to grapple with Prohibition, as illegal speakeasies thrived, drawing increasing attention from law enforcement. In the realm of science, excitement grew over the latest advancements in aviation, with Charles Lindbergh's recent transatlantic flight inspiring new interest in commercial air travel.
